agricultural modernization on laboring families by showing that management practices and contractual arrangements are ultimately molded by local conditions--cultural perceptions of a fair exchange, familial obligations and roles, availability of housing, bargaining power in the home and in the market, kin networks, and information flows--in interaction with national and global influences. Harvesting Coffee, Bargaining Wages will be of primary interest to anthropologists and sociologists, geographers, political scientists interested in explicit and implicit contract formats, and economists intrigued by the possibility of integrating social variables as contextual aspects of management strategies. Sutti Ortiz is Associate Professor Emerita of Anthropology, Boston University.\u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.16153\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.16153","language":"eng","modified":"2025-08-16T08:24:13Z","published":"1999-01-01","publisher":"University of Michigan Press","subject":["Sociology","Class Studies","Latin American Studies","Anthropology","Economics:Labor, Health, and Educational Economics"]},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/8g84mq52t/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/8g84mq52t/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/37720h03h/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/4f16c633n/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/4f16c633n/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/4f16c633n/full/400,/0/default.jpg","width":400,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-s